definition.value: A macromolecule composed of repeating m-phenylenediethylene units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating cyanoethylene units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating (2-propyl-1,3-dioxane-4,6-diyl)methylene units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating (methylimino)[6-(methylamino)borazine-2,4-diyl]units.
A diblock copolymer composed of adjacent blocks of poly(methyl methacrylate) and polystyrene.
Pyrimidine substituted at C-2 by a sulfanyl group.
The hydroxypyrimidine that is pyrimidine mono-substituted at C-2 by a hydroxy group.
A diisocyanate compound with the two isocyanates linked by a hexane-1,6-diyl group.
A morphinane alkaloid that is a derivative of morphine with a 2-morpholinoethyl group at the 3-position.
A 1,3-oxazole compound having a 2-furyl substituent at the 2-position, an ethoxymethylene group at the 4-position, and an oxo group at the 5-position.
The organic chloride salt of cetyltrimethylammonium.
A diblock copolymer composed of adjacent blocks of polystyrene and poly(N-isopropylacrylamide).
A macromolecule composed of repeating 1-[(2-hydroxypropyl)carbamoyl]-1-methylethylene units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating diethylcarbamoylethylene units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating dimethylcarbamoylethylene units.
A polymer carrying two reactive end-groups.

A quaternary ammonium salt in which a positively charged nitrogen is substituted by three (omega-hydroxy)poly(oxyethane-1,2-diyl)groups and one stearyl group, the counterion being phosphate. It is commonly used as a constituent of hairsprays.
A macromolecule composed of repeating acyliminoethylene units and terminated by a hydroxy group. Prepared via ring-opening polymerisation of a 2-oxazoline.
A macromolecule composed of repeating acetyliminoethylene units and terminated by a hydroxy group. Prepared via ring-opening polymerisation of 2-methyl-2-oxazoline.
A macromolecule containing saccharide side-groups.
A macromolecule composed of linked carbazole units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 3,6-linked substituted or unsubstituted carbazole units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 3,6-linked carbazole units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 2,7-linked substituted or unsubstituted carbazole units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 2,7-linked carbazole units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 1,8-linked substituted or unsubstituted carbazole units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 1,8-linked carbazole units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 3,9-linked substituted or unsubstituted carbazole units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 2,9-linked substituted or unsubstituted carbazole units.
The acyl group formed from benzylpenicillin.
A macromolecule composed of repeating substituted or unsubstituted indolo[3,2-b]carbazole units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating thiophene or substituted thiophene units linked at the 2-and 5-positions.
A macromolecule composed of repeating substituted or unsubstituted fluorene units linked at the 2- and 7-positions.
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from O-(N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl)-L-serine.
The residue formed from O-[N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->6)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl]-L-serine
The residue formed from O-[N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->6)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl]-L-threonine
A non-proteinogenic L-amino acid that is N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine linked via an alpha glycosidic bond to the O at position 3 of L-serine.
A L-threonine derivative that is N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine linked via an alpha glycosidic bond to the O at position 3 of L-threonine.
A non-proteinogenic L-alpha-amino acid that is N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->6)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine linked via an alpha glycosidic bond to the O at position 3 of L-serine.
A non-proteinogenic L-alpha-amino acid that is N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->6)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine linked via an alpha glycosidic bond to the O at position 3 of L-threonine.
A cyclic ketone and diether that is a dibutyl ether derivative of squaric acid.
A primary arylamine that is p-xylene substituted at the 2 and 5 positions by amino groups. It is formally a reduction product of 2,5-dimethyl-1,4-benzoquinonediimine.
A 5-membered heterocyclic compound, which is substituted in the 2-position with a methyl group and which is often used as a monomer in polymerisation reactions.

A hydrochloride that is the dihydrochloride of 4,4'-[1,3-phenylenebis(diazene-2,1-diyl)]di(benzene-1,3-diamine). Bismarck brown Y is a metachromatic dye which stains acid mucins yellow. It is also a constituent of Papanicolaou's EA solutions, used for cervical, and other smears.
Azobenzene substituted at each of the phenyl 4-positions by an amino group.
An azo dye with a structure consisting of acetanilide substituted on the 4-position of the phenyl group with a 6-hydroxy-m-tolylazo group.
A diamine in which the two amino groups are substituted into toluene at the 2- and 5-positions.
